lass=headings><font color=#A0B0E0>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uantoxia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Antoxia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/2/02 4:38:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4604.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Epic Quest Question! Maestros room.</span><hr size=1> The Book of Souls.<br><br>Its in Maestros room in Hate. Is it possible to go there using SH? or will I get detected? Will Hide fade when I pick up the book? IOW shuld I wait for a raid or can it be done pretty safe with just a port and SH?<br><br>Anybody that has experience with this plz tell me about it.<br><br>Antoxia<br><br>51 Rake <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utipadaknife.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TipaDaKnife</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/2/02 5:57:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4604.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Epic Quest Question! Maestros room.</span><hr size=1> Yes, it is possible to get there with hide/sneak. I did it that way, solo in Hate. Hide will fade when you pick up the book. You can go with a raid and pick up the book safely when Maestro and his minions are dead, but it's a lot more fun to do it alone. I was in Hate maybe three minutes. If I had to do it all over again, I would have stayed longer and taken more screenshots (I have only the one showing me alone in Hate).<br><br>I was lucky, I encountered no mobs along the way who could see hide/sneak...<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uantoxia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Antoxia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/2/02 9:49:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4604.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Epic Quest Question! Maestros room.</span><hr size=1> Thats very neat. Think I ll try it. Anybody has any idea what mobs see through SH?  I have heard rumors about the litches. Can anybody confirm or deny this. Maby add other mobs. I have also heard talk of gate potions. anybody know where to get theese and how much they go 4? Otherwise just log out at entrance I gess :-)<br><br>Antoxia<br><br>51 Rake <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umakekakkatslave.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Makekak Katslave</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/2/02 2:26:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4604.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Epic Quest Question! Maestros room.</span><hr size=1> I used sneak hide to get my book also. I went up alone with no raid going. Just had a wiz friend port me up then he gated back out. I took along an insta cast gate potion. Snuck up to the bedroom and had to wait about and hour for the book to spawn. Seems there was a raid earlier in the day. When book spawned i picked it up, put in bag and clicked on gate potion. <br>POOF i was outta there. you can buy insta gate potions in town or have someone make them for you.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utibly.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tibly</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/2/02 4:42:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4604.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Epic Quest Question! Maestros room.</span><hr size=1> Will this be considdered an exploit?<br><br>Lets say I duel a friend and die. loot some copper incase stuff goes bananas. Gate up with a Wiz. SH to room and get a friend to Rez me after I get the book.<br><br>Am I missing anything? I am kind of sleepy so I might not be thinking stright. :-)<br><br>Antoxia<br><br>51 Rake <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uthornyeq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ThornyEQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/2/02 6:56:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4604.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Epic Quest Question! Maestros room.</span><hr size=1> Rezzing time is precious time you're exposed after getting the book. you might as well get your hands on a player-made gate potion then (takes longer to cast than a rezz. but either way you're exposed too long). Yes, you can hide immediately after picking up the book, but if a mob made you, 10 seconds may be more time than you have.<br><br>You want insta-cast gates to get you out of there ASAP after pilfering the book. Unless the mob hits you exactly when you're casting the potion, it will go off and you will gate out. Even if it does interrupt you, just take another hit or two and drink up again.<br><br>The only ones I'm aware of that are insta-cast are:<br><br>-- Gate potion from vendors (gate back to bind point, 1250pp or so)<br><br>-- Leatherfoot Raider's Cap (quest in Rivervale, 1 charge of ring of commons, may be able to purchase it, but unlikely; quest is a pain)<br><br>-- Cazic gate potion (dropped by a lizard in Feerrott, gates you to CT wizzie spire, may be purchaseable, but not sure how much)<br><br>Good luck to you. I'm going to try this myself, perhaps this weekend. I have a Cazic gate potion and the wizzie is going to be waiting to evac me outa there; I'm not braving the maze in the new CT. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uprodigious.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Prodigious</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/2/02 8:34:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4604.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Epic Quest Question! Maestros room.</span><hr size=1> just fyi i'm certain picking up the book doesn't break hide. i made it to the book and back through a fully spawned hate. i have also picked up several ground floor items on my wizard with invisibility spell on, and it didn't break it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ureztarn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Reztarn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/2/02 9:45:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4604.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Epic Quest Question! Maestros room.</span><hr size=1> grab a shiny brass idol ( I feel like a broken record ) for the trip too.  That 14 seconds invunerable can be used to dash to the book if there is a see invis mob standing infront of it and give you heaps of time to grab the book and invis.<br><br>Tizla <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucaeildylanena.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caeildy Lanena</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/2/02 11:21:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4604.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Epic Quest Question! Maestros room.</span><hr size=1> Duelling wont work. Res time is only 5 mins.<br><br>Have a real death and accept the 96% res back if you're keen enough.<br><br>Also, hide does not drop when you pick up the book. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unortherner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Northerner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/3/02 5:36:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4604.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Epic Quest Question! Maestros room.</span><hr size=1> Even of you get out clean, an instant-gate potion is perhaps the most valuable thing you can ever own.  I still always carry a CT potion, it is an instant get-out-of-jail-free card.  I know where it is and in what bag and I'd bet I could whip it out and cast before Nimble ever wore off.<br><br>Nah, I've eaten a few dozen deaths without burning it but having that available opens a world of possibilities.  Group with idiots (the ones you can't even trust for CR/Rezzes), go to planes p/u thingies... generally feel immortal.  In a pinch, actually hotkey the potion by putting it in a main slot and such.  Hihi, nearly unkillable here, /bird Lord Empirrrarrrrr Seru.<br><br>That all said, take one on your jaunt and it's not really a nailbiter, it's a fun romp.  I always loved scouting PoH anyways and going from IZ to the book is a perfect compromise of tough and fun.  I'd wager anyone I can do it 9/10 though now that I know the way well. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=syntero>syntero</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/5/02 11:24:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4604.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Epic Quest Question! Maestros room.</span><hr size=1> Just wondering if anyone has a reliabe map... for someone who's never been to the zone....<br><br>I haven't been able to locate one.<br><br>Thanks. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utillaintheslacker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tillain the Slacker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/5/02 12:02:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4604.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Epic Quest Question! Maestros room.</span><hr size=1> BTW library had an excellent map of hate before, never checked lately but it was there. <br><br>As far as the hate solo trip, it does break hide but doesn't break sneak. Have wizzie port up and gate out or evac if they are a chicken. You sneak up get book when mob is turned, re-hide sneak back to SS and cast your gate potion, Done. I know i have done it, btw for the ease of cost make Thurg gate potions they are easy to make and it may be a timed spell but you will gate out real easy sitting on wall. I have done it twice on a fully spawned hate, easy as pie. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=syntero>syntero</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/5/02 2:43:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4604.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Epic Quest Question! Maestros room.</span><hr size=1> *nods*<br><br>Ok I found a map of PoH.. several...<br>but they all just give the rooms letters A-Z and 0-9...<br>noone has decided to share whats in what room... or if so,<br>Which room is which.<br><br>I am thinking more along the lines of porting in....<br>Hide/Sneaking my way to the book.. grabbing it.. and potioning out.<br><br>But it won't do me any good if I don't know which room I need to go to <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Thanks for any help.... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uantoxia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Antoxia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/6/02 6:41:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4604.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Epic Quest Question! Maestros room.</span><hr size=1> Yes a better map with info on where the Maestros room would be great. I have also found the map of Hate on Allakazham <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/maps/Plane_of_Hate.htm">everquest.allakhazam.com/...f_Hate.htm</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> Maby someone can tell us others witch letter is the correct building. Or post a link to a better map.<br><br>Btw have anybody som info on who sees through SH? will it be the same as normal invis to con the mobs? If indiff they cant see and scrowls they see through?<br><br>Antoxia<br><br>51 Rake <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uvyxn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>vyxn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/6/02 3:05:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4604.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Epic Quest Question! Maestros room.</span><hr size=1> liches and scorn banshees are the only 2 things that see through S/H. <br><br>Go throught the forums I know there is a map with the best route in it.  Do a little more research before you go All the information to do it is in here multiple times. <br><br>Good luck!... It was a fun 2-3 minutes. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br><br>Vyxn<br><br>*edit*  Just bumped the thread you need. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uvyxn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>vyxn</A> at: 4/6/02 3:09:06 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utifftif.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tifftif</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/6/02 6:00:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4604.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Epic Quest Question! Maestros room.</span><hr size=1> Kind of funny when you think of it..now that CT's been revamped, gating there would be rather pointless, considering you'd be slaughtered worse than in hate.<br>Unless it puts you somewhere safe in CT, of course.. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uxepante.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xepante</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/7/02 12:03:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4604.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Epic Quest Question! Maestros room.</span><hr size=1> Gating into CT is actually a lot better than Hate when you think about it.  Worse comes to worse you can get a necro to zone in to CT and summon you a lot easier than you could in Hate.  With that said, shortly after the zone upgrade we finished a little stint on VS in KC and I had a wizzy TL me to CT just for the heck of it.  As soon as you land hit sneak / hide.  If you take a couple of steps backwards on the pyramid you have time to cast any number of slow casting gate potions.  (Heck if you have a crazy friend you could dual and get the OT hammer to proc before getting agro'd there... well.. I wouldn't bet the farm on that one.)  But in general, a non planar necro could summon you out of CT, or since your heart will be pumping already, just dodge the two mobs in the maze that see through hide and walk out of there. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umisah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>misah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/8/02 5:55:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4604.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> thurg gate potions</span><hr size=1> Thurg gate potions are so easy to do it hurts....<br><br>I'm not sure on the thurg faction needed to aquire the final container to combine the potion...i did it at ally<br><br>start by bringing up pottery. this took me 30 minutes making medium then large bowls. Skill of 140 is recommended for no fails on the potions.<br><br>in a pottery wheel, combine 3 crystaline silks, 2glass shards (bought of a dorf in the bank in thurg) and 1 small brick of velium. Take that vial and fire it in the kiln with a HQ firing sheet. head over to the potion vendor (turn right when you leave the bank, head down and its a house on the left) and ask the vendor &quot;what velium vapors&quot;. She will give you a container. combine your fired vial and 2 small pieces (the little red stackable ones) of velium to make a thurg gate potion.<br><br>potion takes 10 seconds to cast. It also has a minimum required level on the potion of something silly like level 60. Rest assured i have used the potions since lvl 51 and they have never failed for me... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utillaini.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tillaini</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/8/02 6:46:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4604.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: map of hate</span><hr size=1> looking at allakhazam's map, when you come out of the zone, head to the east wall and, if you were using normal invis or camo for the gate up, drop it there in the southeast corner for your hide/sneak.  counting the buildings along the way, proceed north until you reach the building labeled 6.  now head west between buildings 6 and F.  you should see the fountain (labeled as 8 ) once you pass these buildings.  the map i followed showed to go to the left around the fountain although i don't know if it makes a difference or not.  that's just the way i went.  a little ways further is the maestro's house, building D.  as soon as you go inside, stay to your right and there will be a staircase there.  stay to the inside of the stairs, away from the wall, to avoid aggro through the walls if the patrol should happen to pass at that time.  once at the top of the stairs, head straight until you reach a wall.  staying near the wall, now head to your left.  the first room you see is the bedroom.  i had a scorned banshee up when i went through there the first time but you can avoid it easily enough.  the nightstand is over on the far side of the room, on your right hand side.  if the book is laying there, grab it and instant-gate out.  if your using a thurg potion with the casting time, sneak over to the southeast corner of the room (opposite the nightstand and around the bed), wait for the scorned banshee to finish pacing the room and once it's back on the far side of the room, click the potion.  you should have plenty of time to gate out this way and not attract any unwanted attention.  if the book isn't up, this corner also seems to be the safest place i found to camp out and return to later.  just be ready to hit hide &amp; sneak as soon as you appear back in game.<br><br>full gear run!  woot!  best time i've had in game yet!<br><br>Tillaini D'Sombras<br>53 rake<br>White Dragons <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udalador.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dalador</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/9/02 7:02:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4604.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: map of hate</span><hr size=1> Is it still useful to use the CT Gate potion now,,,, esp after the Revamp of CT? From what I have seen you need a Full Group of High 50's just to do zone in, would hate to try to get from Wizy Spire to Zoneout. But I could be wrong <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rolleyes --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eyes.gif ALT=":rolleyes"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukalabastin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kalabastin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/9/02 11:09:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4604.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: map of hate</span><hr size=1> There is another gate potion that can be made with 122 pottery<br><br><br>vail of velium mist or something like that .. do a search bah here<br><br><br><br><!--EZC